name: Starbucks Rochester Park
author: Orange
review_text: Mobile order took 11 min to complete though the app states 3-7 min. Only 2 person working. There’s a queue.

name: Starbucks Rochester Park
author: Jay Rin
review_text: Ordered an Emperor’s Cloud (grande) and a venti hot water, but both were served in the same grande cup. When questioned, the staff insisted the smaller cup was “venti” and even pressured me to pay for it. This is unacceptable – misleading customers and refusing to acknowledge mistakes. Totally unprofessional and reflects poorly on the Starbucks brand.

name: Starbucks Rochester Park
author: SB Lee
review_text:
Starbucks Rochester Park is a hidden gem! Located in a two-storey colonial-style black & white bungalow, it has plenty of seating, including a lovely open-air balcony on the second floor surrounded by greenery. Perfect for a peaceful coffee break!

Great spot to relax, work, or catch up with friends.

name: Starbucks Rochester Park
author: Jonathan Chandra
review_text: Extremely disappointed at this Starbucks. Had the matcha latte for $8.50. Firstly, the matcha latte was very very disappointing: never had matcha latte that tasted more like a bad concoction of water and matcha powder. The place itself is very nice: tucked away behind rows of colonial bungalows and greeneries. However, it was very run down. The wifi portal was not working: I could not login through my phone as the portal did not show me the login button. I had to wait for the staffs to show up at the counter before my drinks order were processed. It is sad as this place has a very great potential given its location, only if they step up their game.

name: Starbucks Rochester Park
author: Oswald Huang
review_text: Lovely place with lovely drinks and lovely atmosphere for a chat with friends. Lots of students grinding hard on a Sunday afternoon, really inspiring.

name: Starbucks
author: Nishadi Banduthilaka
review_text: One of the best Starbucks outlets I’ve been to! The staff are incredibly friendly and welcoming. Their warm smiles and cute little messages on my drink always brighten my day. Fast, efficient, and genuinely heartwarming service every time!

name: Starbucks
author: Yuqi Wang
review_text: Had a great experience at this Starbucks! Staff member Ezriq was incredibly friendly—always smiling and showing such a positive attitude. His warm service really made my visit more enjoyable. Great coffee, and even better hospitality. Keep it

name: Starbucks
author: Leigh
review_text: the drinks here are pretty standard for starbies but the staff here are super sweet and friendly! there's a nice seating area around the location too :)

name: Starbucks
author: Salman Jaffer
review_text: Lovely staff, well made coffee, fair prices

name: Starbucks
author: Michelle Yeoh
review_text: Best prices in SG with comfy environment and aesthetically appealing surroundings. Only open during weekdays till 7pm

name: Kyuukei Coffee | Gillman Outpost
author: 是无名
review_text:
Hideout! Great and friendly for cyclist and motorcyclist. Of course for public transport a little challenging for the venue. Car, park nearby and enjoy.

Nice coffee and great owners' personality. They rented the place from the triumph motor and so you get to enjoy the bikes and vespa around. Pretty cool.

Maybe it's still new, pastries and bites are a little limited for now. But certainly great coffee.

name: Kyuukei Coffee | Gillman Outpost
author: LAM CHUAN
review_text: Love the coffee. Always something new to surprise me. Crew are super friendly. Takes a while to get your coffee especially when the gym mob just finished their session, but absolutely worth the wait. Lovely atmosphere, surrounded by some fine two wheeled machines of desire.

name: Kyuukei Coffee | Gillman Outpost
author: Lovely Putri
review_text: A hidden gem. Cozy interior, great drinks, and friendly staff. Feels like a soft reset kind of place. Highly recommend and shoutout to Eugene, the barista, who did a really great job👍🏻

name: Kyuukei Coffee | Gillman Outpost
author: Julian Chow
review_text:
Came across this place on a weekend. Will return on weekdays when it's open to review.

Nice service, tried an iced latte on a hot afternoon.  The staff provided a small mug of iced water unprompted, which is really thoughtful.

They also serve curry rice for lunch. Hopefully they'll do well and thrive here.

name: Kyuukei Coffee | Gillman Outpost
author: Kah Wang Tan
review_text:
Located in the middle of Gilman Barracks and I didn’t know it’s a bike shop where they sell bikes and accessories. Limited seatings both inside and outside the place.

Got the long black and I like the hinge of fruitiness in it and suitable for those who don’t like your black coffee being too sweet.

name: Starbucks - Westgate
author: Jacky Tan
review_text:
I ordered 3 slices of cakes to eat in. But only one hour dining. What a service! So crude. Keep on chasing customers away.

For those can’t find seats, next time come earlier. Or just wait for seats.

A group of aunties doing knitting for an hour above still there and no one is chasing them. The staff is not doing their work properly. Disgrace.

name: Starbucks - Westgate
author: Ricky Seah
review_text: Second time here but I'm very pleased with the shift manager and service staffs Maloy, Ayed, Azlin, Siti and Faraz who are very courtesy, friendly and helpful in every ways of assisting us in our ordering and recommendation. For sure I go for my creamy chicken foldovers in all Starbucks as this is my favourite and my family and friends also like it very much.

name: Starbucks - Westgate
author: Jerlves Lee
review_text:
I would really like to apologise & a big thank you to the Starbucks team at Westgate.

I accidentally spilled over my coffee and created a mess for the team to mop the floor.
And to my surprise,  they offer me another coffee for me which I have kindly rejected them.

Kudos to Westgate Starbucks team for going the extra miles which its really hard to see more of the extended service beyond which this is me,  customer at fault.

Once again
Thank you every team members of Westgate Starbucks

name: Starbucks - Westgate
author: Florence Leow
review_text:
🟢 Starbucks
3 Gateway Drive
#02-04, Westgate mall
Singapore 608532

🟢 Location ➡️This Starbucks cafe is located on Level 2 of the Westgate mall.

🟢 Nearest train station ➖️ Jurong East MRT station. ● Westgate mall is connected to Jurong East Station via sheltered walkways.

🔵 Decor
************
🔵This Starbucks at Westgate mall features a modern and spacious interior with warm wooden accents and a mix of seating options.

🔵  There is a variety of seating, including wooden tables and chairs & some sofa lounge-style seating. ◼️ The decor includes a checkered floor pattern, wooden slatted ceiling features & several framed pictures hanging on the back wall.

🟫 Drinks
************
🟨 My friend and I ordered two Hot Cafe Lattes and I requested for a single shot of espresso for each mug. The result was a creamy, mild and delicious cafe latte with just a tinge of slight bitterness.

🟤 Service = 🟤 The staff were pleasant and efficient.

name: Starbucks - Westgate
author: Inseparable Food
review_text: Food and drinks tasted good! Place is big, many seats. Good place to go to chill, talk and eat.
